-- CEO Benmosche Says If We Were Simple, ‘Then We Wouldn’t Be AIG’
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r   a n d   E l i z a b e t h   B u n n
-- 2013-02-22T13:53:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-22/ceo-benmosche-says-if-we-were-simple-then-we-wouldn-t-be-aig-.html
Chief Executive Officer  Robert
Benmosche , who has narrowed American International Group Inc.’s
focus by selling units, said there are limits to how much can be
done to limit the insurer’s complexity.  “Some days you wish you could have a simple company,” he
said on a conference call today held by the New York-based
company. “But then we wouldn’t be AIG.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
